            "kind": "other",
            "title": "Nha Rong Wharf",
            "title_i18n": {},
            "details": "Nha Rong Wharf (officially the Ho Chi Minh Museum - Ho Chi Minh City Branch) is a significant historical landmark located at the junction of the Saigon River and the Ben Nghe Canal. It is famously known as the place where a young man named Nguyen Tat Thanh (who later became President Ho Chi Minh) set sail on his quest for national liberation.",
            "details_i18n": {},
            "image_subtitle": null,
            "image_subtitle_i18n": {},
